The image of every compact set under a continuous function is compact, and the image of every connected set under a continuous function is connected.

The map formula_163 is uniformly continuous if for every formula_108 there exists formula_176 such that

Every uniformly continuous map formula_163 is continuous. The converse is true if formula_167 is compact (Heine–Cantor theorem).

Uniformly continuous maps turn Cauchy sequences in formula_167 into Cauchy sequences in formula_165. For continuous maps this is generally wrong; for example, a continuous map
